# Booker conventions

## Lifecycle

- `start_booking_loop(booking)` / `stop_booking_loop(booking)` — register `Booker` in `__CURRENT_THREADS`.
- CRUD on active bookings in `views.py` must start/stop threads to match `is_active`.
- Always use `app.app_context()` inside threads; reload `Booking` from DB each loop iteration.

## Booking loop (summary)

1. `_get_datetime_to_book(last_book_date, dow, time)` — next class in Madrid TZ.
2. `_TimeWaiter` until booking window (`offset` + `available_at`).
3. `get_scraper(email, cookie)` → `scraper.book(url, datetime, type_class)`.
4. Success → update `last_book_date`, `booked_at`, persist `user.cookie`, notify mail/push.

## Waiters

- `_TimeWaiter` — sleep until datetime (window, penalization backoff, network retry).
- `_EventWaiter` — `scraper.wait_until_event` for SSE (`changedBooking`, `changedPizarra`).

## Sync (no Booker thread)

- `sync_wodbuster_bookings(user)` — mirror API bookings into `WodBusterBooking`.
- `sync_training_descriptions_for_date(user, date)` — `ClassTrainingDescription` cache.

